soc.message

Class SOCMovePiece

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCMessageForGame
        • soc.message.SOCMessageTemplate4i
          • soc.message.SOCMovePiece
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SOCMovePiece
extends SOCMessageTemplate4i
    Client player is asking to move, or server is announcing a move of, a piece on the board to a new location. Currently, ships are the only piece type that can be moved.

    Scenario SC_FTRI has a rule about moving trade ports, but those are part of the board layout and not considered pieces.

    From requesting client:

    Requests moving a piece that's already on the board to a new location. The server will announce to all players with SOCMovePiece if piece can be moved, or reply to the requester with SOCCancelBuildRequest.

    From server to all game members:

    Announces a player is moving a piece that's already on the board to a new location. This is a response to all player clients, following a player's SOCMovePiece request. If pieceType == ship, the client should also print a line of text such as "* Joe moved a ship."

    If MovePiece leads to Longest Route player changing, server sends that after its MovePiece message: SOCGameElements(LONGEST_ROAD_PLAYER).

    Since:
    2.0.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin <jeremy@nand.net>
    See Also:
    SOCMoveRobber, Serialized Form

        public SOCMovePiece(java.lang.String ga,
                    int pn,
                    int ptype,
                    int fromCoord,
                    int toCoord)
             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Create a SOCMovePiece message.
        Parameters:
        ga - the name of the game
        pn - the player number; ignored if sent from client
        ptype - piece type, such as SOCPlayingPiece.SHIP; must be >= 0
        fromCoord - move piece from this coordinate; must be >= 0
        toCoord - move piece to this coordinate; must be >= 0
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if ptype < 0, fromCoord < 0, or toCoord < 0
